          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-22 11:48:29" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to decide a question of legal right or wrong, and thus determine the innocence or guilt of the accused and assign appropriate punishment or retribution{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to decide a legal question</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to act as a judge</Gloss>
                <Gloss>making a legal decision</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to arrive at a verdict</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to try a case (in the passive to stand trial)</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The process of legal judging is often expressed idiomatically. In Africa, one of the standard phrases for judging is ‘to cut a palaver,’ but other expressions in other languages may be ‘to find guilt,’ ‘to point the finger at wrong,’ or ‘to untangle strife.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
